  ;; ── Design notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (text "ES7243E AUDIO ADC NOTES:\n\n1) Power:\n   AVDD = PVDD = 3V3_ANALOG (ultra-low noise LP2985)\n   DVDD = 3V3_MAIN\n   Separate analog/digital grounds, single-point star at U7 output\n\n2) Input configuration (single-ended from SI4732):\n   LINP = signal (via C17 AC couple + R6+C19 anti-alias)\n   LINN = 0Ω to AGND\n   RINP = signal (via C18 AC couple + R7+C20 anti-alias)\n   RINN = 0Ω to AGND\n   R8/R9 = 100kΩ bias to VMID (mid-supply reference)\n\n3) Anti-alias filter: R6/R7 = 1kΩ, C19/C20 = 10nF C0G\n   -3dB cutoff fc = 1/(2π × 1k × 10n) = 15.9kHz\n   Adequate for 44.1kHz Nyquist (22.05kHz max audio)\n\n4) I2S mode: Slave (BCLK and LRCK driven by ESP32)\n   BCLK = IO18, LRCK = IO19, SDOUT → I2S_DIN (IO21)\n   Sample rate: 44100 Hz, 16-bit, stereo\n   MCLK: connect to ESP32 MCLK output (IO0) at 11.2896MHz\n   or configure ES7243E for BCLK-derived clock (no MCLK needed)\n\n5) I2C address: AD0 pin → GND = 0x10; AD0 → VDD = 0x11\n   Shared I2C bus with SI4732 (different addresses)\n\n6) VMID/VREF: internal reference, bypass to AGND with 10uF each\n   Place close to IC, use shortest path to AGND plane"
    (at 200 100)
    (effects (font (size 1.7 1.7)) (justify left))
  )
)
